01:20:21.358 --> 01:20:24.278
But, Nico, that pride may kill all of us.

01:20:30.701 --> 01:20:32.494
Swallow your pride.

01:20:35.372 --> 01:20:37.624
Choke on it, if you have to.

01:20:38.584 --> 01:20:41.503
- Lay it down, please.
- You know something?

01:20:42.212 --> 01:20:46.300
There's nothing in this world
that I wouldn't do for my family.

01:20:46.717 --> 01:20:48.552
Nobody will harm us.

01:20:49.678 --> 01:20:52.181
I don't want you to worry. Okay?

01:21:30.177 --> 01:21:33.263
Not even you can hit him
at this range, Nico.

01:21:34.765 --> 01:21:36.642
That wasn't the plan, Nelson.

01:21:36.725 --> 01:21:38.185
Close range?

01:21:39.186 --> 01:21:42.648
It'd never work. It's rigged.
Scanned every 35 seconds.

01:21:42.731 --> 01:21:45.651
I was thinking of a claymore on the roof...

01:21:46.026 --> 01:21:47.069
No!

01:21:47.569 --> 01:21:50.698
The roof is wired, too.
Sensors every 15 feet.

01:21:51.782 --> 01:21:53.158
Okay. Now you can move.

01:21:53.242 --> 01:21:56.578
- It's me. You don't have to treat me like...
- Slow!

01:21:56.662 --> 01:22:00.165
Come on, let's get the fuck out of here.
Move! Slow.

01:22:00.374 --> 01:22:03.836
You even look at me funny,
you're in the river, Toscani.

01:22:03.919 --> 01:22:07.214
I figured you'd do your recon
from this building.

01:22:09.299 --> 01:22:12.636
- You're looking fit.
- I'm getting a bit of a tire.

01:22:12.970 --> 01:22:15.597
- Is that your own tailor?
- Hong Kong.

01:22:16.265 --> 01:22:18.517
- You've come a long way.
- Yeah.

01:22:19.268 --> 01:22:20.561
Just walk.

01:22:22.271 --> 01:22:23.605
I don't believe you.

01:22:23.689 --> 01:22:27.776
What's so hard to believe?
I want to help you, you dumb guinea.

01:22:28.485 --> 01:22:30.863
I've been trying to talk
some sense into you.

01:22:30.946 --> 01:22:32.906
You're still "Fox the Fixer."

01:22:32.990 --> 01:22:37.077
If I wanted to cap you,
I'd save myself all this damn chitchat.

01:22:37.619 --> 01:22:40.789
I'd make big points for myself
if I brought your scalp in.

01:22:40.873 --> 01:22:43.042
Shit, I'd be White House material.

01:22:43.208 --> 01:22:45.419
Is that what Zagon is,
one of your basement boys?

01:22:45.502 --> 01:22:49.381
Zagon's a rancher. 4,000 acres
in Costa Rica. Beautiful place.

01:22:49.465 --> 01:22:54.178
Beautiful place, huh? Was that bought
with opium money from the triangle?

01:22:54.720 --> 01:22:57.264
And a ton of coke a week
from other places.

01:22:57.348 --> 01:23:00.934
Which he funnels here through Salvano.
The company getting it's cut, of course.

01:23:01.018 --> 01:23:02.519
Legal tender.

01:23:03.896 --> 01:23:06.899
So war is still the greatest business, huh?

01:23:07.566 --> 01:23:11.737
These guys have started and financed
every war we've ever fought.

01:23:11.862 --> 01:23:15.991
Nobody would believe me if I told them
the bankers were the CIA.

01:23:16.825 --> 01:23:19.536
Come on, Toscani, don't preach to me.

01:23:19.995 --> 01:23:22.206
So the senator couldn't be bought,
could he?

01:23:22.289 --> 01:23:27.002
He was gonna expose your plans to invade
Nicaragua with your fucking coke money.

01:23:27.252 --> 01:23:29.713
So the Agency clears Zagon
to cap his ass, right?

01:23:29.797 --> 01:23:31.757
Just keep walking, asshole.

01:23:31.840 --> 01:23:34.802
So some poor, innocent priest finds out.
He comes here.

01:23:34.885 --> 01:23:38.389
But you can't kill the senator
until you know if the "padre" has talked.

01:23:38.472 --> 01:23:43.268
So Zagon comes in, "Tell me," with his
little doctor bag. Only by then, I'm in on it.

01:23:43.686 --> 01:23:47.314
And you fucking know
I'm gonna recognize his handiwork.

01:23:48.524 --> 01:23:51.193
If your name would've been Joe Smith,
I never would've caught it.

01:23:51.276 --> 01:23:54.071
But how many Nicola Toscanis are there?

01:23:54.613 --> 01:23:58.617
Tell me something, old buddy.
Do we kill our own senators now?

01:23:59.785 --> 01:24:01.203
Why not? The Romans did.

01:24:01.286 --> 01:24:04.206
- Are we the fucking Romans?
- We're an empire, too.

01:24:04.331 --> 01:24:06.959
You don't believe that shit for a minute.

01:24:07.042 --> 01:24:08.627
Just walk. Go!

01:24:19.513 --> 01:24:20.931
Hold it, Nico.

01:24:23.559 --> 01:24:26.562
- Here's your key, sir.
- My buddy will drive.

01:24:33.319 --> 01:24:35.029
You know something?

01:24:35.112 --> 01:24:39.825
In Europe, they're trying some 80-year-old
camp guard for Nazi war crimes.

01:24:40.617 --> 01:24:43.620
All around our country,
they got guys on Death Row...

01:24:43.704 --> 01:24:46.457
...for murdering one, two, three guys.

01:24:46.832 --> 01:24:49.752
And they probably deserve
what they're gonna get.

01:24:49.835 --> 01:24:51.503
But you and I...

01:24:51.587 --> 01:24:54.006
...we know people
that are personally responsible...

01:24:54.089 --> 01:24:57.426
...for the death
of 50,000 non-military personnel.

01:24:58.093 --> 01:25:01.847
Librarians, teachers, doctors,
women, children, all dead.

01:25:02.806 --> 01:25:05.225
We've wiped out entire cultures.

01:25:05.476 --> 01:25:06.935
And for what?

01:25:07.478 --> 01:25:12.066
Not one CIA agent has ever been tried,
much less accused, of any crimes.

01:25:13.442 --> 01:25:17.446
You guys think you're above the law,
but you ain't above mine.

01:25:19.490 --> 01:25:23.285
Nico, we don't have time for this.
Get in the goddamn car.

01:25:46.392 --> 01:25:50.646
I've been waiting for the day
I'd catch up with this motherfucker.

01:25:57.194 --> 01:25:59.571
Salvano and his scumbag dealer.

01:26:00.990 --> 01:26:02.992
What a team we got here.

01:26:03.200 --> 01:26:05.452
I told you, you'd never be the man.

01:26:05.536 --> 01:26:08.122
Nelson, we've been looking for you.

01:26:09.498 --> 01:26:11.041
I see that you...

01:26:11.667 --> 01:26:13.419
...found our friend.

01:26:13.502 --> 01:26:14.962
Thanks, Fox.

01:26:15.421 --> 01:26:17.715
I didn't bring him. I swear it.

01:26:18.215 --> 01:26:20.926
You two must have had a lot to talk about.

01:26:21.010 --> 01:26:23.512
Reminiscing about the good old days?

01:26:23.595 --> 01:26:24.847
Stay still!

01:26:26.223 --> 01:26:28.225
Just fucking don't move.

01:26:28.559 --> 01:26:30.811
Nelson, bring our friend in.

01:26:35.691 --> 01:26:37.693
Come on, be a good boy.

01:26:39.028 --> 01:26:40.446
Dive, Nico!

01:26:56.962 --> 01:26:58.839
Get that motherfucker!

01:27:15.564 --> 01:27:16.732
Move it!

01:27:20.027 --> 01:27:21.195
Get him!

01:27:51.308 --> 01:27:53.310
Stop the car, you fuck!

01:27:59.525 --> 01:28:01.902
Stop the car, you piece of shit!

01:28:03.028 --> 01:28:04.321
Stop it!

01:28:22.339 --> 01:28:23.716
Fox's car!

01:29:08.635 --> 01:29:10.304
{y:i}He's on the ramp now.

01:29:10.387 --> 01:29:13.557
{y:i}He's coming out the Wabash entrance.
{y:i}Get there, Deep Throat.

01:29:13.640 --> 01:29:16.185
{y:i}Roger, Spike Leader. We read you.

01:29:25.235 --> 01:29:27.029
Get out of the car!

01:29:27.196 --> 01:29:28.906
I want him alive.

01:29:36.372 --> 01:29:37.790
He's clean.

01:29:38.415 --> 01:29:40.000
Bring him over.

01:29:41.794 --> 01:29:42.836
Let's go!

01:29:46.215 --> 01:29:50.135
We're out of here.
Abandon the vehicles and get out of here.

01:29:50.928 --> 01:29:53.931
Tommy, hurry up! Get in.
We're out of here.

01:30:08.988 --> 01:30:12.241
{y:i}Now, our honored guest,
{y:i}Senator Ernest Harrison.

01:30:32.761 --> 01:30:36.432
I hope this don't take too long
'cause I'm getting hungry.

01:30:43.689 --> 01:30:46.567
This is bullshit. We've got work to do.

01:30:47.359 --> 01:30:50.321
All work and no play
makes Jack a dull boy.

01:30:52.406 --> 01:30:56.660
We've got an hour before we say good-bye
to the honorable senator.

01:30:57.036 --> 01:31:00.289
You know, you've got to learn
to take time to...

01:31:00.956 --> 01:31:02.750
...smell the roses.

01:31:03.292 --> 01:31:06.545
How are you gonna do him?
Do him in the motorcade...

01:31:07.004 --> 01:31:09.798
...or pass him through a hotel kitchen?

01:31:18.932 --> 01:31:20.434
Put his face up.

01:31:22.770 --> 01:31:24.021
Hold it up.

01:31:25.105 --> 01:31:27.733
Here you go, Toscani."Dr. Feelgood."

01:31:42.289 --> 01:31:46.209
I've used these little beauties many times
to extract information.

01:31:46.293 --> 01:31:48.628
For the first time in my life...

01:31:48.962 --> 01:31:51.590
...I'm gonna do it just for the fun.

01:31:54.092 --> 01:31:56.178
Get the fuck away from me!

01:32:34.684 --> 01:32:35.977
Let him go.

01:32:49.199 --> 01:32:51.534
Toscani, my sleeping beauty...

01:32:52.160 --> 01:32:54.579
...you should've killed me
when you had the chance.

01:32:54.662 --> 01:32:57.165
You're too fucking dumb, asshole.

01:33:01.961 --> 01:33:03.505
Jake! Look out!

01:33:41.114 --> 01:33:42.991
Say something. Nico?

01:33:45.118 --> 01:33:46.119
Is there a doctor here?

01:33:46.202 --> 01:33:48.246
Quick! Call an ambulance!

01:33:52.041 --> 01:33:56.796
Agent Neeley, FBI. We've got a problem,
but we don't know what it is, yet.

01:34:01.426 --> 01:34:04.012
Please, Senator Harrison, this way.

01:34:04.804 --> 01:34:09.058
{y:i}We are standing in front of the home
{y:i}of Police Sergeant Nico Toscani.

01:34:09.142 --> 01:34:12.520
{y:i}Behind me, the entourage
{y:i}of Senator Harrison is arriving.

01:34:12.604 --> 01:34:16.983
{y:i}Lots of security here. We have police
{y:i}officers on the scene and federal agents.

01:34:17.066 --> 01:34:20.069
{y:i}Of course, there is concern
{y:i}of a possible assassination attempt.

01:34:20.153 --> 01:34:24.073
{y:i}That's why you've got
{y:i}so many law enforcement officers here.

01:34:28.328 --> 01:34:31.539
- This is Senator Harrison. Nico Toscani.
- How do you do?

01:34:31.623 --> 01:34:33.458
Please, don't get up.

01:34:33.833 --> 01:34:35.668
Detective Toscani...

01:34:35.877 --> 01:34:39.756
...I just felt compelled to come
and thank you personally...

01:34:39.839 --> 01:34:43.259
...and to assure you that we'll use
every resource available...

01:34:43.343 --> 01:34:45.219
...to bring these men to justice...

01:34:45.303 --> 01:34:49.641
...and to ensure that this type of behavior
will never be tolerated again.

01:34:51.309 --> 01:34:53.102
That would be nice.

01:34:53.519 --> 01:34:57.482
Let me introduce Roberta Alspaugh
of the Fifth Circuit Court.

01:34:57.899 --> 01:34:59.108
How do you do, ma'am?

01:34:59.192 --> 01:35:01.527
Are you sure you're well enough?

01:35:02.737 --> 01:35:05.823
I'm ready to talk if you're ready to listen.

01:35:06.241 --> 01:35:07.492
All right.

01:35:08.201 --> 01:35:11.829
- Miss Jackson, I'll leave you now.
- Senator, thank you.

01:35:13.498 --> 01:35:17.627
- We'll be leaving for Washington.
- Hey buddy, we'll be back later.

01:35:20.880 --> 01:35:22.423
Mr. Toscani...

01:35:22.715 --> 01:35:26.052
...can you tell us about
your military background?

01:35:30.223 --> 01:35:33.559
In 1973, I worked for
a special operations group...

01:35:34.852 --> 01:35:37.021
...in Vietnam and Cambodia.

01:35:37.897 --> 01:35:40.775
I was involved with gathering intelligence.

01:35:40.858 --> 01:35:45.196
All of the members of this team
were doctors recruited by the CIA...

01:35:45.905 --> 01:35:49.409
...and trained at a secret camp
in Langley, Virginia.

01:36:01.629 --> 01:36:05.216
{y:i}Gentlemen, whenever you have a group
{y:i}of individuals...

01:36:05.675 --> 01:36:07.885
{y:i}... who are beyond any investigation...

01:36:07.969 --> 01:36:12.265
{y:i}... who can manipulate the press,
{y:i}judges, members of our Congress...

01:36:13.224 --> 01:36:17.395
{y:i}... you'll have within our government
{y:i}those who are above the law.

